<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A Victorian man was disgusted after finding a slug inside a half-cauliflower he purchased from his local Woolworths supermarket. </p>

<p>Michael Robinson bought the cauliflower from the Lara Woolworths, northeast of Geelong, on Wednesday before making the find at home.</p>

<p>Mr Robinson took to the Woolworths Facebook page to express his disgust. </p>

<p>Victorian man Michael Robinson was disgusted when he found a slug living inside a half-cauliflower he had bought from his local Woolworths in Lara, northeast of Geelong (pictured)</p>

<p>'Not happy Woolworths, the not so fresh people, had this slug and all its pooh through my cauliflower,' he wrote.</p>

<p>'Looks like I will be now shopping at your opposition. One very unhappy long time Woolies customer.'</p>

<p>A Woolworths spokesperson responded to Mr Robinson's post saying the company understood his disappointment. </p>

<p>'We're sorry to see your cauliflower in that condition and we definitely share your disappointment in this matter,' the reply read.</p>

<p>'With our Fresh or Free guarantee, you're eligible for a full refund or replacement.</p>

<p>'We hope that your next experience with us is a positive one.'  </p>

<p>Mr Robinson took to the Woolworths Facebook page to share his disgust saying the slug had left poo all over the inside of the cauliflower (Lara Woolworths pictured)</p>
